Suppose that $$A=\left( 
 \begin{array}{rrr}
1 & 2  & -1  \\ 
0 & 0 & 2  \\ 
-1 & -2 & 3  \\ 
2 & 4 & 0 \end{array}
\right)$$ and $$B=\left( 
 \begin{array}{rrr}
0 & 1  & 1  \\ 
2 & 2 & 0  \\ 
0 & 3 & 2 \end{array}
\right).$$ Which of the following matrices has rank $3$?

Find $x$ and $y$ such that $\left( \begin{array}{rr}
-2 & 1 \\ 
3 & -4 \end{array}
\right)\left( \begin{array}{rr}
x & 2 \\ 
1 & y \end{array}
\right)=\left( \begin{array}{rr}
-3 & 1 \\ 
2 & -14 \end{array}
\right)$.

